name: Metapod
description: Inside the shell, it is soft and weak as it prepares to evolve. It stays motionless in the shell.

name: Weedle
description: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.

name: Pidgeotto
description: It has outstanding vision. However high it flies, it is able to distinguish the movements of its prey.

name: Butterfree
description: It collects honey every day. It rubs honey onto the hairs on its legs to carry it back to its nest.

name: Bulbasaur
description: The seed on its back is filled with nutrients. The seed grows steadily larger as its body grows.

name: Charmander
description: The flame on its tail shows the strength of its life force. If it is weak, the flame also burns weakly.

name: Venusaur
description: By spreading the broad petals of its flower and catching the sun's rays, it fills its body with power.

name: Charizard
description: If CHARIZARD becomes furious, the flame at the tip of its tail flares up in a whitish-blue color.

name: Wartortle
description: It is recognized as a symbol of longevity. If its shell has algae on it, that WARTORTLE is very old.

name: Blastoise
description: It deliberately makes itself heavy so it can withstand the recoil of the water jets it fires.

name: Vileplume
description: It has the world's largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

name: Primeape
description: If approached while asleep, it may awaken and angrily give chase in a groggy state of semi-sleep.

name: Weepinbell
description: Even though it is filled with ACID, it does not melt because it also oozes a neutralizing fluid.

name: Dodrio
description: It collects data  and plans three times as wisely, but it may think too much and become immobilized.

name: Dewgong
description: Its streamlined body has little drag in water. The colder the temperature, the friskier it gets.

name: Exeggutor
description: Its three heads think independently. However, they are friendly and never appear to squabble.

name: Pinsir
description: With its horns, it digs burrows to sleep in at night. In the morning, damp soil clings to its body.
